@startuml class-state-model
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because the state model is two heterogeneous stores (a relational :doc entity
'' with «unique»/«schema-less» stereotyped attributes, plus a nested ephemeral app-db map) bound by one
'' amber bridge field; PlantUML classes carry stereotypes + colour + composition arrows that express
'' "app-db OWNS these slices" and "the bridge field couples the two stores" — Mermaid classDiagram cannot
'' colour members nor stereotype individual attributes.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title vinary-viewer state model — DataScript :doc entity (SSOT) + app-db (ephemeral UI)\nlinked by the amber :ds/rev bridge field

skinparam class {
  AttributeFontColor #1A1A1A
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}

'' ---------- DataScript: the single source of truth for documents/tabs ----------
package "DataScript conn  (vinary.app.ds)" <<Folder>> #line:743F7B {

  class "schema" as Schema << (S,#A45BAD) >> DATASCRIPT_TINT {
    :doc/path  →  {:db/unique :db.unique/identity}
    .. that is the ENTIRE schema ..
  }

  class ":doc  (one per open file)" as Doc << (E,#A45BAD) entity >> DATASCRIPT_TINT {
    + :doc/path : string  <<unique identity>>
    --
    :doc/kind  : "markdown" | "image" | "text"  <<schema-less>>
    :doc/text  : string?   (absent for images)  <<schema-less>>
    :doc/html  : string?   (rendered output)     <<schema-less>>
    :doc/error : string?   (retracted when gone) <<schema-less>>
    :doc/open? : boolean   (is it a tab?)         <<schema-less>>
    :doc/order : long      (tab position)         <<schema-less>>
  }
  note bottom of Doc
    «schema-less» = a plain scalar attribute that needs
    NO schema entry. DataScript requires schema only for
    :db.unique, :db.type/ref, and :db.cardinality/many.
  end note
}

'' ---------- app-db: ephemeral UI only ----------
package "app-db  (re-frame; vinary.app.db/default-db)" <<Folder>> #line:4C66AE {

  class "app-db root" as AppDb << map >> APPDB_TINT {
    :ds/rev : long = 0   <<bridge>>
    :ui : { … }
  }

  class ":ui" as Ui << map >> APPDB_TINT {
    :active-path : string?  (the focused tab)
    :theme : "spacemacs-dark" | "spacemacs-light"
    :active-heading : id?   (scroll-spy)
    :sidebar-visible? : boolean
    :tree : {:root :files}  / :tree-filter : string?
  }

  class ":ui/history  (Command stack)" as Hist << map >> APPDB_TINT {
    :stack : [path …]
    :idx   : long = -1
  }

  class ":ui/find" as Find << map >> APPDB_TINT {
    :visible? : boolean = false
    :query : string = ""
    :count : long = 0
    :idx   : long = 0
  }

  class ":ui/input / :ui/palette\n«now available»" as Input << map >> {
    :input {:mode :sequence :count …}
    :palette {:open? :source :query …}
  }
}

AppDb *-- Ui          : :ui
Ui    *-- Hist        : :history
Ui    *-- Find        : :find
Ui    *-- Input       : :input / :palette

'' the amber bridge: a transaction on conn bumps :ds/rev, which conn-reading subs depend on
Doc -[#B1951D,thickness=2]-> AppDb : **d/listen!** → [:ds/changed]\n**(update db :ds/rev inc)**

note as N1 #FFF6D6
  THE BRIDGE (amber): the two stores are kept in lock-step by one
  field. Every DataScript transaction fires the conn listener, which
  dispatches [:ds/changed] → (update db :ds/rev inc). The subs :tabs
  and :doc/active declare :<- [:ds/rev], so they recompute per tx.
  re-posh is a declared dependency but UNUSED — this hand-rolled
  bridge is the real reactivity.
end note
N1 .. AppDb

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#A45BAD>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| DataScript — single source of truth (documents/tabs) |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| app-db — ephemeral UI state (re-frame) |
  |<#B1951D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| :ds/rev bridge field (DataScript ⇄ re-frame) |
  «schema-less» needs no schema · «unique» = identity key · «now available» = available
endlegend
@enduml
